wikipedia_page.main: Frederick John Champion de Crespigny (12 December 1822 – 25 June 1887) was an English first-class cricketer active 1843–51 who played for Nottinghamshire. He was born in Camberwell; died in Hampton Wick.He was educated at Magdalene College, Cambridge. After graduating he became a Church of England priest and was perpetual curate at Emmanuel Church, Camberwell, from 1850 to 1858, then vicar of Hampton Wick from 1858 until his death.
